<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on algeria 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land algeria on the southern shore of the mediterranean 
is the second largest african country after the sudan its 919595 
square miles 3 times the size of texas are mostly uninhabited 
desert 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people most of the estimated 25 million people are arab and 
moslem with a significant berber minority most live in a narrow 
700milelong fertile coastal strip with one of the highest birth 
rates in the world the annual population growth is 35 percent 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy algeria once earned more than 12 billion a year 
from oil and gas oil prices plummeted in the 1980s while the 
population explosion continued causing severe shortages of 
consumer goods more than 1 million algerians live and work in 
western europe and send home about 400 million a year the 
algerian dinar is worth about 20 cents 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history once part of the ottoman empire algeria remained 
loosely controlled by turkey until the french seized control in 
1830 on the grounds that algerian pirates were interfering with 
international shipping in the mediterranean 
algeria became an integral part of france and 15 million 
french farmers settled in the fertile areas moslems were denied 
equal rights with french citizens breeding resentment that led to 
the revolution 
on nov 1 1954 the underground national liberation front 
attacked french military and civilian installations independence 
came in 1962 after two years of talks with the government of 
president charles de gaulle 
most of the french settlers fled when their land was 
nationalized in 1963 col houari boumedienne the commander of the 
nationalist forces seized power in 1965 and introduced a 
sovietstyle regime harshly critical of the united states and 
israel he became one of the leaders of the nonaligned movement 
boumedienne died in office in 1978 and was replaced by 
thenchief of staff col chadli bendjedid who has softened the 
regime despite opposition from hardliners 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

