canada has lost its patience with us fishermen 
poaching in its territorial water and after years of fruitless 
pursuit has resorted to firing machine gun warnings at one boat 
and boarding another 
on oct 1 canadian fisheries officials fired a 50caliber 
machine gun across the bow of a new bedford scalloper the donna 
lynn and chased it for six hours before giving up 85 miles east of 
nantucket 
the vessel has yet to return to port but canada has asked the 
