<TEXT>
welborn hope an oklahoma poethistorian 
known as the tramp poet because of his extensive travels died 
sunday he was 86 
his first work four men hanging was a historical 
recounting of the april 1909 lynching of four men in ada hope soon 
turned from prose to poetry 
the great river and small was a collection of some of hopes 
short poems including several first published in the saturday 
review of literature 
hopes final work custers reward is scheduled for 
publication next month by the university of oklahoma press 
custers reward is the final work of a poetic trilogy 
detailing the lives of a western family a century ago 
the trilogy began with the prarie ocean and continued in 
beside the chisolm trail 
