90 percent of new jobs 
furthermore the increasingly deregulated global economy tends 
to be more selfregulating the magazine stated with interest 
rates rising in overheated economies to help choke off inflation 
and economic booms thus lessening the severity of booms and busts 
among other predictions for the 1990s 
following recession the economy will enjoy moderate inflation 
and steady moderate growth 
unemployment could fall as low as 4 percent due to the expected 
baby bust that will see workforce growth slow sharply 
the dollar will decline slightly but will bottom out helping 
further trim the us trade deficit 
